(Description)
Given the head of a singly linked list, reverse the list, and return the reversed list.

--- Solution ---
class Solution {
    public ListNode reverseList(ListNode head) {
        ListNode prev = null;
        ListNode curr = head;

        while (curr != null) {
            ListNode next = curr.next;
            curr.next = prev;
            prev = curr;
            curr = next;
        }

        return prev;
    }
}

--- Approach ---
(Key Concept)
The key was making the another prev Linked List.
It stored the every next nodes into the prev Linked List,
then if the prev become the next node of curr Linked List, it naturally reversed the position one by one.
